    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "·         Undertake a mapping exercise of the existing HIV prevention programmes for MARAs and EVAs including  life skills interventions in Nepal\r\n·         Review and revise existing life skills materials for and with young people, to make it gender sensitive, HIV responsive, interactive as well as appropriate for the MARAs and EVAs.\r\n·         Implement the HIV risk reduction and avoidance skills intervention among MARAs[1] and EVAs through sports and recreational activities.\r\n·         Implement adolescent friendly PMTCT and VCT for MARAs and EVAs, specifically girls in selected intervention areas.\r\nCarry out participatory research to monitor behaviour change among the adolescents \r\n \r\n(In 2008 – 2010 CPAP, the funds were managed based on the projects whereas the funds for 2011-2012 has been allocated based on the IRs. Therefore, the budget in this AID management platform is reflected only for 2011-2012).\r\n\r\n\r\n[1] In Nepal context MARAs are identified as - CSW, IDU and MSM"
      },
      "ne": null
    },
